[Student "S"]
{With 12 points you know game is likely, but for now you bid 1\H. Partner rebids 1NT. What do you say next? 

Partner has 12-14 points, balanced. If he is at the top, game could still be there, but you aren't sure where to play. If partner has only 2 \Hs then NT is probably best, but if he has 3 \Hs then you would prefer to play the 8-card Major fit. New Minor Forcing will allow partner to answer both questions for you. So you bid 2\C. Partner answers with 2NT.  

Partner tells you he has only 2 \Hs. He also tells you he only has 12-13 points. So you pass 2NT.}

